<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="117" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1048,1325]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1192,1217]" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, Dai &amp; Li" authorityYear="2014" box="[321,768,1192,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Varicopsella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamiltoni" subGenus="Multispinulosa">
<emphasis box="[321,461,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">Varicopsella</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[477,645,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">Multispinulosa</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[661,768,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">hamiltoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here transferred into the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hamilton" authorityYear="1980" box="[1184,1282,1192,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1184,1282,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">Pedionis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hamilton" authorityYear="1980" box="[1298,1396,1192,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1298,1396,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">Pedionis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It may be easily distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hamilton" authorityYear="1980" box="[602,700,1228,1253]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Pedionis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[602,700,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="117">Pedionis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the unique body coloration of yellow face and pronotum and black forewings; not pointed pygofer and pygofer ventral process with small spines and setae; and the special structure of the dorsal connective.
</paragraph>
